<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>Artificial intelligence and philosophy have more in common than a science usually has with the philosophy of that science.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>If the program is to reason about what it can and cannot do, its designers will need an attitude to free will.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>If the program is to be protected from performing unethical actions, its designers will have to build in an attitude about that.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>Causal relations must also be used for a robot to reason about the consequences of its possible actions.</a>
